CAT(1)                         User Commands                         CAT(1)

NAME
    cat - concatenate files and print them

SYNOPSIS
    cat [OPTION]... [FILE]...

DESCRIPTION
    Copy each FILE to standard output, in order. With no FILE, or when FILE
    is '-', read standard input.

    This is the unmodified GNU coreutils cat(1), ported to Horus and run as a
    ring-3 program from /bin/cat over the fs_server. The shell also has a
    lighter cat builtin; /bin/cat shadows it when present.

OPTIONS
    -n    number all output lines
    -b    number non-blank output lines
    -s    squeeze repeated blank lines
    -E    show a '$' at end of each line

    Run `cat --help` for the full option list.

EXIT STATUS
    0 on success, non-zero on a file that cannot be read.

SEE ALSO
    head(1), tail(1), wc(1), hier(7)
